cyclone.name: FRED
cyclone.current_location: about 15 miles SSW of Caibarién, Cuba

motion.direction: W (expected to turn WNW then NW)

cyclone.trajectory: Moving WNW along the north-central Cuban coast, forecast to pass near or west of the Florida Keys Saturday, then track northwest along Florida’s west coast toward a Florida-Panhandle landfall and move inland across the Southeast U.S.
cyclone.expected_landfall_location: Florida Panhandle (near the Apalachicola/Cedar Key area)

weather_observation.watch_coast: Southwest coast of Florida from Englewood south and east to Ocean Reef (Tropical Storm Watch)
weather_observation.warning_coast: Florida Keys west of Ocean Reef to Dry Tortugas and Florida Bay (Tropical Storm Warning)
weather_observation.impacted_coast: Northern coast of Cuba, the Florida Keys, Florida Peninsula west coast, and Florida Panhandle coastline
weather_observation.wind: Breezy conditions possible mid-week as remnant low passes inland (generally below tropical-storm force)
weather_observation.storm_surge: None expected because the system remains inland well south of Delaware Bay
weather_observation.rainfall: 1–3 inches of rain possible 17–18 Aug, which could cause ponding and minor localized flooding
weather_observation.other_hazards: Very low tornado risk associated with remnant frontal interaction
